cff-version: 1.2.0
title: "LogDx-CI: Benchmarking Log Reduction Tools for LLM Root-Cause Diagnosis"
message: "If you use this benchmark, please cite it as below."
type: dataset
authors:
  - family-names: Qin
    given-names: Bowen
    affiliation: "National University of Singapore"
repository-code: "https://github.com/eyuansu62/LogDx"
repository-artifact: "https://huggingface.co/datasets/eyuansu71/logdx-ci"
url: "https://logdx-bench.github.io/"
abstract: >
  LogDx-CI evaluates whether log reduction tools preserve enough
  evidence for LLM root-cause diagnosis. The benchmark compares 11
  log reducers (raw, tail, grep, rtk-{read,log,err-cat}, two real
  LLM summarizers — llm-summary-v1-haiku (Anthropic) and
  llm-summary-v1-gpt-5-mini (OpenAI) —, and three hybrid routers)
  on 35 real GitHub Actions failure cases spanning eight failure
  categories and seven ecosystems. Diagnoses from three debuggers —
  Claude Haiku 4.5, Claude Sonnet 4.6, and OpenAI gpt-5-mini — are
  scored against AI-drafted, author-verified ground truths using a
  calibrated formula (diagnosis_score_v1_1) covering category
  accuracy, signal-mention recall, file/test recall, forbidden
  claims, and confident-error rate. The headline finding is that
  the top-3 intersection across the three debugger families is
  {hybrid-grep-120k-rtk-tail, hybrid-grep-120k-tail}, and the
  bottom-4 set is also stable across all three families. v1.2 adds
  the cross-family LLM-summary baseline, which becomes the
  agent-loop #1 at 0.749 with 0.37 tool calls per case and
  falsifies the self-call-bias hypothesis. The release includes the
  full corpus, evaluator code, protocol locks, and three
  release-gate scripts that pin canonical state against shim/config
  drift and provider-error class leakage.
keywords:
  - llm
  - benchmark
  - ci-cd
  - log-analysis
  - log-reduction
  - rtk
  - coding-agents
  - root-cause-analysis
